      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1765925546306,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "There are 3 types of Object Oriented Design Patterns -\n    a. Creational patterns - teaches on scalable ways to create objects.\n    b. Structural Patterns - teaches on how to assembles objects and classes into larger structures\n    c. Behavioral Patterns - teaches on responsibilities of each object\n\nCREATIONAL PATTERNS -\n\n   1. Factory Pattern - \n        a. Every class should extend the same interface.\n        b. 1 public static class would be responsible to create the derived class based on user's input\n           and will return the object of type interface.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "There are 3 types of Object Oriented Design Patterns -\n    a. Creational patterns - teaches on scalable ways to create objects.\n    b. Structural Patterns - teaches on how to assembles objects and classes into larger structures\n    c. Behavioral Patterns - teaches on responsibilities of each object\n\nCREATIONAL PATTERNS -\n\n   1. Factory Pattern - \n        a. Every class should extend the same interface.\n        b. 1 public static class would be responsible to create the derived class based on user's input\n           and will return the object of type interface.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
