    {
      "id": "ahcRgMfepo271y5uNnOwQ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 558.6346593078855,
      "y": 2776.8978258755837,
      "width": 1371.199951171875,
      "height": 364.7609775938975,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b2E",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 83956532,
      "version": 1078,
      "versionNonce": 86477702,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1742622226302,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "4. Singleton Pattern -\n    a. It is useful when the object needs to be shared between different classes\n    b. Create a static creation method that acts as a constructor.\n       Under the hood, this method calls the private constructor to create an object and saves it in a static field. \n   \n5. Prototype Pattern -\n    a. This is basically a copy constructor. \n    b. Ideally, every class needs extend an interface with single clone API which would \n       return a new instance of the same class with the exact value of the member pointers.\n       \"return new Class (this)\" \n   \n",
      "fontSize": 24.317398506259835,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "4. Singleton Pattern -\n    a. It is useful when the object needs to be shared between different classes\n    b. Create a static creation method that acts as a constructor.\n       Under the hood, this method calls the private constructor to create an object and saves it in a static field. \n   \n5. Prototype Pattern -\n    a. This is basically a copy constructor. \n    b. Ideally, every class needs extend an interface with single clone API which would \n       return a new instance of the same class with the exact value of the member pointers.\n       \"return new Class (this)\" \n   \n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "MP4jUKFc-_ElCPHdgIVNk",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 553.7588559987278,
      "y": 3164.1270710714803,
      "width": 1422.2332763671875,
      "height": 334.36422946107274,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b2H",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 598018316,
      "version": 2369,
      "versionNonce": 1279527734,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1742357225581,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "STRUCTURAL PATTERNS\n\n1. Adapter Pattern - \n   a. It is useful when you want to when you want to use some other class\n      but its interface isn’t compatible with the rest of your code.\n   b. So, you will create a wrapper interface over the incompatible interface \n      with an intent to call the other class's interface.\n   c. In the below example, Dog act as an adapter. Client requested for a LandAnimal to sayCantFly but our\n      service only has SkyAnimal (and only sayFly). So, we introduced a Dog (which is a wrapper/adapter over SkyAnimal) \n      which explicitly adds 'Cant' and call SkyAnimal's sayFly method\n",
      "fontSize": 24.317398506259835,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "STRUCTURAL PATTERNS\n\n1. Adapter Pattern - \n   a. It is useful when you want to when you want to use some other class\n      but its interface isn’t compatible with the rest of your code.\n   b. So, you will create a wrapper interface over the incompatible interface \n      with an intent to call the other class's interface.\n   c. In the below example, Dog act as an adapter. Client requested for a LandAnimal to sayCantFly but our\n      service only has SkyAnimal (and only sayFly). So, we introduced a Dog (which is a wrapper/adapter over SkyAnimal) \n      which explicitly adds 'Cant' and call SkyAnimal's sayFly method\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
