      "seed": 1920260202,
      "version": 3028,
      "versionNonce": 365664743,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1765925579854,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "\n3. Decorator Pattern -  (Creates Composition)\n   a. The decorator class is essentially a wrapper over the concrete class extending the same interface,\n       adding extra behavior along the way.\n   b. Be mindful that the only difference between decorator and adapter is the \n      decorator extends the same interface as of interested concrete class (in the below example - Expresso) whereas \n      adapter does not extend the same interface as of interested concrete class (in the adapter example - Bird)\n",
      "fontSize": 24.317398506259835,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\n3. Decorator Pattern -  (Creates Composition)\n   a. The decorator class is essentially a wrapper over the concrete class extending the same interface,\n       adding extra behavior along the way.\n   b. Be mindful that the only difference between decorator and adapter is the \n      decorator extends the same interface as of interested concrete class (in the below example - Expresso) whereas \n      adapter does not extend the same interface as of interested concrete class (in the adapter example - Bird)\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
