      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1146216234,
      "version": 4347,
      "versionNonce": 1238990902,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1742399035187,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "\n5. Flyweight Pattern - \n   a. It is exactly similar to proxy pattern in terms of having a responsibility to make a decision whether to \n      call the concrete class or not.\n   b. However, the difference is the flyweight class will not extend the same interface as of concrete class.\n   c. The logical intent for flyweight is to optimize memory whereas intent for proxy is to provide access control\n       to the concrete class.\n\n\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 24.317398506259835,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\n5. Flyweight Pattern - \n   a. It is exactly similar to proxy pattern in terms of having a responsibility to make a decision whether to \n      call the concrete class or not.\n   b. However, the difference is the flyweight class will not extend the same interface as of concrete class.\n   c. The logical intent for flyweight is to optimize memory whereas intent for proxy is to provide access control\n       to the concrete class.\n\n\n\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
