    {
      "id": "3MRnA31vkrrnZpoMcMfsN",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 571.0256207436421,
      "y": 10188.936288610037,
      "width": 1515.86669921875,
      "height": 303.9674813282479,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b4v",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 63549738,
      "version": 3721,
      "versionNonce": 178001898,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1742430936118,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "\n2. Chain of Responsibility Pattern -\n    a. It is a step by step process to complete an objective. All the steps are concrete classes extending the same interface. \n    b. However, every step knows about the next step and makes a decision on whether to call it or not.\n    c. You can imagine it as a linear list with every step aware of the next step in correct order without depending upon them.\n    d. In the below example, Order --> Prepare --> Deliver are steps which knows about the step in front but since it implements\n       CoffeeStep Abstract class, the concrete class of the step is not dependent on another concrete class of the step.\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 24.317398506259835,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\n2. Chain of Responsibility Pattern -\n    a. It is a step by step process to complete an objective. All the steps are concrete classes extending the same interface. \n    b. However, every step knows about the next step and makes a decision on whether to call it or not.\n    c. You can imagine it as a linear list with every step aware of the next step in correct order without depending upon them.\n    d. In the below example, Order --> Prepare --> Deliver are steps which knows about the step in front but since it implements\n       CoffeeStep Abstract class, the concrete class of the step is not dependent on another concrete class of the step.\n\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
